description: Teixera, Mister No’s future brother-in-law, has been killed by Sombra’s men, who want to silence him. Jerry and Vadinho wander in the jungle, fighting against criminals and Indios. In the end, the pilot is aided by an Indio friend and lets Vadinho go, as he has always acted loyally towards Jerry. But an ugly surprise awaits him in Manaus…
name: Nemici per la Pelle

description: Vadinho Moraes, free again, seeks revenge on his ex-partners, who tried to eliminate him. Meanwhile, Gloria has changed her mind, she has got over her brother’s death and again asks Mister No to marry her. Jerry accepts, but his path will once again, and dramatically, cross Vadinho’s…
name: La Gola del Diavolo

description: Mister No goes to a bank with his friend Carmensa just at the very moment when a gang of thieves burst in, led by a nervous individual. Mister No discovers that it is Ratso, a young man he met years before in New York. The police have surrounded the bank and Jerry tries to keep the robbers quiet by telling them all about his meeting with Ratso…
name: Gli Ostaggi

description: After the adventure at Aspen, Mister No returns to New York, but he finds that the situation is not as rosy as he might have liked. The mobster Masulli, who is in league with the corrupt Captain Williams, holds the city in thrall, and life is hard for Jerry (also because his Detective friend Phil Mulligan has been killed by Masulli’s men!). Ratso asks him to collaborate in staging a false kidnapping – of Ratso himself - designed to worm money out of his rich father. But there is an unexpected development…
name: La Città del Crimine

description: Mister No saves Ratso form the kidnappers, who had decided to transform the bogus kidnapping into the real thing, and then moves to the counterattack. He tries to strike a blow at Masulli’s organization and, above all, at one of his men, Jackie, the head of a gang of bikers who hate Mister No. A resurrection from the dead gives him a hand…
name: I Gangsters

description: In the past, we witness the final show-down between Mister No and Jackie (and it is Ratso who saves Mister No’s life). In the present, the net is closing in on Ratso. The police are bent on killing him and Mister No is accused of abetting. But the cowardly, spoilt, neurotic Ratso will have a sudden resurgence of pride.
name: Corsa Verso la Morte

description: Ananga is the evil spirit praised by many Indio tribes. After the palmist Isaura has forewarned Mister No of his meeting with an evil being, our hero receives a visit from Abigail Wolfe, the wife of Peter Wolfe, a strange client who parachuted into the jungle from Mister No’s Piper. Jerry and Abigail go into the jungle to search for Peter, where they undergo strange rituals and meet him…Ananga!
name: Ananga!

description: Ananga, the evil spirit, has reincarnated himself as Wolfe, who brings death to Manaus, killing the beautiful Isaura. Even Wolfe’s wife, Abigail, in the end is possessed by this evil being…Mister No must fight him: but how do you kill a spirit?
name: Lo Spirito del Male

description: Mister No reaches the Antarctic, the immense uninhabited continent covered in ice, travelling with the expedition of Professor Wilson, who intends to follow the same route as the explorer Scott. But their journey is littered with inexplicable accidents…
name: Inferno di Ghiaccio

description: Eventually, after the umpteenth attempt, Professor Wilson reveals the real nature of the journey into the Antarctic. The expedition must locate the mysterious base of the “Ghost”, an extremely powerful secret organization. Our men find it, but here they discover that the Ghost has nuclear warheads at its disposal with which, if the organization’s requests are not complied with, it will destroy…New York!
name: Paura Bianca

description: In the ancient city of Machu Picchu, Professor Perkins discovers a mysterious tower that causes people in the area to have frightening visions. The professor’s daughter, Alison, seems almost possessed by the atmosphere in the place. But the person who may have the key to the mystery is a monk, Brother Rafael, who is haunted by terrible, arcane nightmares…
name: La Fortezza Perduta

description: There’s a curse on Machu Picchu. Trump, one of the Perkins men, steals some jewels and attempts to kill the archaeologist and his faithful men. In the meantime, Mister No, Alison and brother Rafael enter the tower and discover the ancient and terrifying horror that it holds…
name: La Torre Maledetta

description: After being closed for a long period, the Manaus Opera House reopens its doors. But the company which is to perform Verdi’s “Rigoletto” is the same one that, fifteen years earlier, was involved in a disaster: the baritone Erik Maelstrom disappeared without a trace. Who is the mysterious masked character that is now wandering around the theatre, spreading terror?
name: Il Fantasma dell'Opera

description: Horror spreads like wild fire in the Manaus Opera House. The conductor is murdered and Olinto Rigetti, Mister No’s baritone friend, also risks his life. The key to the mystery is the prima Donna, the soprano Maria Arghidas. The mysterious masked man kidnaps her, and it is to her that he reveals his disturbing identity…
name: Il Passaggio Segreto

description: Patrick Moore, an important American atomic scientist, has left the States and has gone to Brazil, to join the sect of the “Risen from the Dead”. The CIA make use once again of Delia (who pretends to have been kidnapped by the “Risen from the Dead”) to persuade Mister No into finding Moore. The pilot comes up against an old acquaintance, O Bispo, and meets Moore. But this time it will be Mister No who plays a trick on the CIA…
name: L'Uomo che Sapeva Troppo

description: A Dakota aeroplane, that crashed years before in the jungle, is worshiped like a divinity by the Indios. Patricia is also wandering around in that zone of the forest, looking for a precious pre-Columbian sculpture. Kidnapped by the Indios, the beautiful archaeologist calls Mister No and Esse-Esse for help. But if her two friends want to set her free, they must demonstrate that they have been sent from the heavens, by making the Winged God …fly once more!
name: Mister No 100: Giungla!

description: Mister No has re-baptized her Laura. She is a girl Jerry found in the jungle who, after having suffered a severe shock, has no memory. Strange characters try to kidnap her while Laura, in her nightmares, mentions the mysterious “Moon mountains”: where does she come from?
name: Le Montagne della Luna

description: The girl with no past is kidnapped by Doctor Moraes, who attended to her in hospital and who is obsessed with her. But the doctor is found dead. Led by a small clue, Mister No arrives in Chile, in the hottest and most arid place on earth: the Atacama moon mountains!
name: I Misteri di Atacama

description: Eventually, Mister No discovers the identity of the girl without memory. She is called Luisa Parker, the daughter of the powerful millionaire Joseph Parker, who keeps her secluded in the immense Parkerville estate. Luisa says she is a botanist and claims to have found a revolutionary discovery…
name: Commando!

description: The Almanac opens with the part dedicated to the mysteries of 1988 and closes with a monographic dossier devoted to the mysterious history of the world, from the Big Bang to Year Zero. The central part is occupied by a comic-strip of Martin Mystère, in which we discover what would be the consequences of an epidemic causing the immediate disintegration of the bodies of those who die…
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1989

description: In the comic-strip, another adventure for the Detective of the Impossible: our planet must face invasion by an extraterrestrial real-estate agency. The only man on Earth capable of undermining this cunning alien menace is the developer and real-estate speculator Donald Trump! To complete the Almanac, there is an editorial section on all the mysteries of 1989 and a monographic dossier dedicated to the future that awaits us, from 1990 to 2086.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1990

description: In the comic-strip adventure in the middle of the volume, Martin and Java are searching for a lost Terrestrial Paradise, but the discovery of Eden – which came about by sheer chance during the Gulf War – is the fore- runner to a catastrophic disaster. As for the editorial part, in addition to the usual section, which presents a round-up of all the mysteries of 1991, there is also a dossier on the mysteries of the Near East, the land of the three revealed religions.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1992

description: The editorial part is dedicated to all the mysteries of 1992, and to a dossier on the mysterious Orient, whereas in the comic-strip story, the Detective of the Impossible will have to deal with the Yakuza, with magic Japanese swords, with Ninja warriors, and above all, with “the nine-handed cut”: a very secret position which renders anyone invincible in the martial arts.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1993

description: A new graphic project for the Almanac of Mystery, but the traditional approach of the Almanac is retained: an initial part dedicated to the recent events; a conclusive section with a first monographic dossier on the secrets of Italy, and a central part dedicated to a comic-strip adventure, in which the Earth is in grave danger, due to the threat from the Titans, extraterrestrial creatures driven by the worst of intentions.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1994

description: The comic-strip of this Almanac takes us into the bowels of Milan, together with a group of urban speleologists. Unfortunately the secret underground passages below the capital city of Lombardy are also of interest to a group of terrorists, who are preparing a terrible subversive plot. The Almanac is completed by an editorial section on the mysteries of 1994 and by a second dossier dedicated to the “Italian mysteries”.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1995

description: The Almanac of Mystery contains a comic-strip story that forms a bridge between Australia and ancient Egypt; the story also mentions the mysterious Hanging Rock the true origin of the boomerang is revealed. Martin visits again the Altrierjinga, i.e. the “World of Dreams” of the Australian Aborigines. In the editorial part, along with the usual section of topical subjects, there just had to be a dossier on Australian mysteries.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1996

description: In addition to the usual review of the mysteries of the past year, this Almanac presents a dossier on fantastic, monstrous and mysterious animals. The comic-strip also focuses on an animal, the Dodo: one of the favourites of Lewis Carroll (author of “ Alice in Wonderland”) and an extinct animal par excellence. In our days, there are some signs suggesting that in parts of South America, a colony of dodo have survived and there is someone prepared even to kill for the sake of locating them and getting hold of them.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1997

description: From this edition of the Almanac of Mystery onwards, we begin to follow the fantastic adventures of Cigale, an ancestor of Martin Mystère, but above all that of his faithful advisor, Docteur Mystère. In the Milan of the nineteenth century, the two experience a classic serialized adventure, rich in unexpected developments and spectacular happenings. The Almanac is completed by the traditional editorial section, in which there stands out a curious dossier on the reports of mysterious happenings published by American daily newspapers from 1890 till 1940.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1998

description: The editorial part of this Almanac of Mystery is divided between topical articles and a dossier dedicated to the mysteries of the old West. Mysteries which also figure in the comic-strip story, which presents the second adventure of Docteur Mystère, set, appropriately enough, in the prairies of the New World. In addition to the brilliant ancestor of the Detective of the Impossible, we also find the treacherous Radetzky, who is arranging a diabolical plot to become the emperor of the United States of America.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 1999

description: This year Docteur Mystère and Cigale continue their adventures even on the moon. In an atmosphere of science-fiction typical of Jules Verne, we will once again see our heroes contending with the hard-working Chinese entrepreneur Cin’Ghei and the treacherous Radetzky. The dossier of this Almanac is dedicated to the “Mysteries of 2000”, or rather how the pioneers of science-fiction imagined our future.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 2000

Dolly interviews Lazlo, Raj and Clam

4. Summer Fun! (activity pages)
name: Camp Lazlo

description: "Treasure Hunt" by Kathleen Webb and Dan DeCarlo: Someone's laid out a scavenger hunt for Betty and Veronica, but you won't believe who... or why! "Once is Enough" by George Gladir & Dan DeCarlo: Life is a carnival, but not for Betty, when Veronica makes her sit through home videos of her trip to the fair! "Back to School Blues" by Webb and DeCarlo: After an illness, Veronica plans to wow Riverdale High in her stunning new fashion. The only problem is, after 12 girls wore it during Veronica's absence, it's stunningly old! Plus, "Oldies But Goodies" by Webb and DeCarlo: The cheerleaders don 1940s uniforms in an effort to convince the school to get them new ones, but they're soon buying their own, with the profits they make selling the 40s uniforms to the female teachers!
name: Treasure Hunt; Once Is Enough; Back To School Blues; Oldies But Goodies

description: "The Height Of Fashion": Betty and Veronica rise to the occasion 'literally' when they start wearing eight inch platform shoes! "The Bake-off": The heat is on, but Veronica insists on staying in the kitchen to challenge Betty to a bake-off! "A Change Of Mood": Betty proceeds as if the glass is half full, but Veronica's determined to drink that glass empty! "A Purpose In Life": As they reflect on their friendship, Betty and Veronica acknowledge that opposites attract!
name: The Height Of Fashion; The Bake-Off; A Change Of Mood; A Purpose In Life; Scooter Tooter; Puzzled

description: "Bad Girl Gone Good": Veronica is in another rip-roarin' mood, but her bad behavior is sure to backfire! "The Best Policy": Archie decides that total honesty will impress the girls... but someone should have told him holding your tongue beats brutal honesty any day!
name: Bad Girl Gone Good; The Best Policy

description: "The Big Scene": Betty gets a summer job at the Riverdale Library and starts a "teen lounge" where teens can enjoy not only books but magazines, comic books and CD's, too! "Digging For Buried Treasure": It's buccaneer fun when Betty and Veronica flash back to the "Little Archie" days, reminiscing about how they used to pretend they were pirates and made Archie "walk the plank!" "A Cold Day In July": On the hottest day of the year, Mr. Lodge employs a snow-making machine to cool the girls off, but when it gets out of control, the whole town is in the "deep freeze!"
name: The Big Scene; Digging gFor Buried Treasure; Little Archie; A Cold Day In July

description: "Rabid Rivals" (by George Gladir & Jeff Shultz): All is fair in love in war... even if you're at a fair, as Betty and Veronica learn when Archie and Adam engage in a battle of one-upmanship there! "So Real It's Surreal" (by Kathleen Webb & Jeff Shultz): Veronica puts on her bikini, orders a frozen hot dog on a stick and gets ready for school... in the summer!
name: Rabid Rivals

description: "Old Flame!": Betty and Veronica plan a surprise reunion between Ms. Grundy and her high school sweetheart/debating team colleague... but whether their reunion is "sweet" is open to "debate!"
name: Old Flame

description: They saved the world in LOCKJAW & THE PET AVENGERS…what’ve they been doing since? Find out in this super-sized special featuring Lockjaw, Redwing, and the rest of your favorite Pet Avengers take center-stage in their own spotlight adventures!
name: Beginnings And Endings

description: They saved the world in LOCKJAW & THE PET AVENGERS…what’ve they been doing since? Find out in this super-sized special featuring Lockjaw, Redwing, and the rest of your favorite Pet Avengers take center-stage in their own spotlight adventures!

description: MARVEL DIGITAL COMICS EXCLUSIVE The Falcon's most trusted ally is hot on the heels of a jewel thief but that's the least of Redwing's problems. This time around, Redwing must also deal with a persistent super fan named Melvin! Will the pestering pigeon cause Redwing to lose his perp? Or will Melvin turn out to be the sidekick of the year? Find out tomorrow!
name: Birds of A Different Feather

description: MARVEL DIGITAL COMICS EXCLUSIVE Everyone's favorite pet dragon, Kitty Pryde's Lockheed, takes center stage! The little fire breather's set to torch your exclusive digital pages with high flying hijinks! This Pet Avenger's one winged wonder you won't want to mess with! Find out why!
name: Prom Queen
